free_txt: The effect of the 34S in the target was estimated by
ignoring any resonance structure in its cross section
and assuming that its contribution to the observed
yield was due to Rutherford and hard sphere
scattering only.
The contribution from hard sphere scatt. to Rutherford
scatt. cross section at 1.400 MeV used for norm. is
less that 1% forward of 125 deg. and 2.3% at 161.7 deg.
